===Theatre===

Two plays were produced in the 1970s that were based on thinly-veiled versions of the Krays:
* &quot;Alpha Alpha&quot;, by Howard Barker in 1972
* &quot;England England&quot;, a musical by Snoo Wilson with music by Kevin Coyne and directed by Dusty Hughes in 1977, starring Bob Hoskins and Brian Hall in the lead roles.
===Music===
* The song &quot;Last of the Famous International Playboys&quot; (1989) by English musician Morrissey was inspired by what he saw as media glamourization of the Krays, and refers to both brothers by name in the lyrics. Reggie Kray mentioned the song in his autobiography, stating: &quot;I liked the tune, but the lyrics in their entirety were lacking a little.&quot; Morrissey responded: &quot;I can&#x27;t get away from critics.&quot;

